      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NEW SHUFFLE (6) kicked off his campaign with a placing from this barrier at Menangle before a midfield finish to flying mare Captains Mistress at Listed level. Has switched back to the Chircop yard since and looks very well placed with a big class drop. Hard to knock the consistency of MY LITTLE BO (7) who led from a similar barrier and scored by 4.6 metres at this venue last time, giving her three wins and two placings from her last five starts. Tactics will be crucial from this draw but with even luck she could keep the ball rolling. KOMODO (4) returns to a venue where he owns a decent record and could be close to a win after placing in three of his last four starts. HES ALL TORQUE (2) draws well and is another that looks to have the hoof on the till after back-to-back placings, the latest at this circuit when he started on the back row.",
